  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Now kubelet creates the container log by joining `(pod metadata)+(container name)+(containerID)` [(here)](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L731), and then mount it to container by adding it to `bind` in `HostConfig` [(here)](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L739), and pass it to container when start [(here)](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L775).\n\nIt means that we could only creating container log directory after `create` the container, because we can only get `containerID` after creating it. [(here)](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L714)\n\nHowever, as is mentioned in issue #20454, `HostConfig` at container start will be deprecated from 1.10, and will be completely removed by 1.12. Although for 1.10 we could still use it, there will be quite a lot of annoying warning log in `docker.log`:\n\n```\ntime=\"2016-02-03T20:28:57.867598821Z\" level=warning msg=\"DEPRECATED: Setting host configuration options whe\nn the container starts is deprecated and will be removed in Docker 1.12\"\ntime=\"2016-02-03T20:28:58.330340910Z\" level=warning msg=\"DEPRECATED: Setting host configuration options whe\nn the container starts is deprecated and will be removed in Docker 1.12\"\ntime=\"2016-02-03T20:39:38.184004120Z\" level=warning msg=\"DEPRECATED: Setting host configuration options whe\nn the container starts is deprecated and will be removed in Docker 1.12\"\ntime=\"2016-02-03T20:39:38.624884402Z\" level=warning msg=\"DEPRECATED: Setting host configuration options whe\nn the container starts is deprecated and will be removed in Docker 1.12\"\n```\n\nSo after 1.12 we could only pass `HostConfig` to container create. If so, we should\n- not rely on containerID when creating the container log directory\n- Or, find some other ways to mount directory to container after it is created but not started.\n\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-node \n",
